The paper deals with the problem of multiclass classification, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The focus on constructing logarithmic depth trees suggests that the paper may also fall under the category of data structures (cs.DS). The use of decision trees for classification is often applied in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL), which are also potential sub-categories for this paper.
